WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.000
♪ Who's gonna help when the danger overwhelms ♪

00:03.000 --> 00:05.000
♪ And the mysteries are piled high? ♪

00:05.000 --> 00:07.000
♪ Who's gonna be around, never gonna let you down ♪

00:07.000 --> 00:09.000
♪ When you're on a wild ride? ♪

00:09.000 --> 00:11.000
♪ Your friends are always by your side ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:15.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:15.000 --> 00:19.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:19.000 --> 00:21.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek ♪

00:21.000 --> 00:24.000
♪♪

00:24.000 --> 00:26.000
Kelsey: "'You cannot stop me!

00:26.000 --> 00:29.000
My power comes from another dimension!'"

00:29.000 --> 00:31.000
[ Cackles ]

00:31.000 --> 00:33.000
"Hurthok cackled, and he took out his quantum-axe,

00:33.000 --> 00:37.000
and he sliced, and he sliced, and he sliced!"

00:37.000 --> 00:39.000
[ Muffled rock music playing ] Man! You're good

00:37.000 --> 00:39.000
at tellin' stories.

00:39.000 --> 00:41.000
I mean, I never hear a soundtrack in my head

00:41.000 --> 00:42.000
when I'm readin'.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.000
Wait. I can hear it, too.

00:44.000 --> 00:48.000
[ Music continues ]

00:48.000 --> 00:50.000
This way.

00:50.000 --> 00:53.000
[ Music volume increases ]

00:53.000 --> 00:57.000
♪♪

00:57.000 --> 00:58.000
What's wrong, Craig?

00:58.000 --> 01:00.000
Is it this terrifying abandoned barn?

01:00.000 --> 01:04.000
Oh, wait! The bird incident.

01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
Hey. Sorry we forgot.

01:06.000 --> 01:07.000
Let's just go around.

01:07.000 --> 01:10.000
♪ When you listen close enough ♪

01:10.000 --> 01:12.000
♪ You're not asking why it hurts ♪

01:12.000 --> 01:15.000
♪ You're wondering if it hurts too much ♪

01:15.000 --> 01:16.000
♪ Well, come on ♪

01:16.000 --> 01:21.000
[ Instrumental break ]

01:21.000 --> 01:23.000
♪ Give it a shot if you stand it alone ♪

01:23.000 --> 01:25.000
♪ Give it a shot ♪

01:25.000 --> 01:31.000
♪ You can make it on your ooooown ♪

01:31.000 --> 01:34.000
♪ If all you want is a license to go ♪

01:34.000 --> 01:35.000
♪ Give it a shot ♪

01:35.000 --> 01:40.000
♪ You won't suffer through no moooore ♪

01:40.000 --> 01:41.000
Aah! Aah! Aah!

01:41.000 --> 01:44.000
♪ Give it a shot if you stand it alone ♪

01:44.000 --> 01:47.000
♪ Give it a shot, you can make it on your ♪

01:47.000 --> 01:49.000
♪ Give it a shot if you stand it alone ♪

01:49.000 --> 01:53.000
♪ Give it a shot, you can make it on your own ♪

01:53.000 --> 01:54.000
[ Cheers and applause ]

01:54.000 --> 01:55.000
-All right! -That was awesome!

01:55.000 --> 01:56.000
-Yeah! -Wow!

01:57.000 --> 01:58.000
Uh, thanks.

01:58.000 --> 02:01.000
We're David, Emma, Katie, and Daoud.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
We're Bad Moves! Cool!

02:03.000 --> 02:07.000
We're Craig, JP, and Kelsey, and we're good kids.

02:07.000 --> 02:09.000
Well, thanks for watching, kids.

02:09.000 --> 02:10.000
Is this a club?

02:10.000 --> 02:12.000
Did we run all the way to the city?

02:12.000 --> 02:14.000
Nah, this is just our house.

02:14.000 --> 02:15.000
We call it the Pizza Crust Collective.

02:15.000 --> 02:18.000
We live here -- with, like, 15 other people.

02:18.000 --> 02:21.000
It's cool, 'cause we all like music and pizza.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.000
Oh, so it's like a forever sleepover,

02:23.000 --> 02:26.000
but nobody tells you to shut your mouth and go to sleep.

02:27.000 --> 02:28.000
Sometimes that happens.

02:28.000 --> 02:29.000
But, yeah, it's pretty cool.

02:29.000 --> 02:31.000
We all help out and share everything,

02:31.000 --> 02:34.000
although the peanut butter belongs to Michelle.

02:34.000 --> 02:36.000
I mean, we could eat it, but, you know...

02:36.000 --> 02:38.000
[ Bass-guitar note plays ]

02:38.000 --> 02:40.000
Sorry. It's cool.

02:40.000 --> 02:44.000
Why don't you give it a try? Go ahead.

02:44.000 --> 02:45.000
[ Bass-guitar note plays ]

02:45.000 --> 02:46.000
Cool!

02:47.000 --> 02:49.000
But it must be impossible to play a whole song.

02:49.000 --> 02:50.000
You have to do that a million times.

02:50.000 --> 02:53.000
Yeah. I mean, did you guys go to college

02:53.000 --> 02:55.000
for, like, 20 years to learn all that?

02:55.000 --> 02:58.000
Nah. I actually picked it up from my brother.

02:58.000 --> 03:01.000
He played bass, and I thought it was very cool.

03:01.000 --> 03:04.000
Now I play guitar, and  I am very cool.

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
Yeah, I was in high-school orchestra,

03:06.000 --> 03:08.000
but I didn't like being told what notes to play,

03:08.000 --> 03:09.000
so I joined a band.

03:09.000 --> 03:11.000
I'll play a "G" whenever I want.

03:11.000 --> 03:13.000
[ Guitar riff ] You hear that,

03:11.000 --> 03:13.000
Mr. Samson?!

03:13.000 --> 03:15.000
I used to carry around a pair of drumsticks.

03:15.000 --> 03:17.000
Everyone called me "Sticks."

03:17.000 --> 03:21.000
So I was, like, a drummer before I was a drummer.

03:21.000 --> 03:22.000
Anyone can play.

03:22.000 --> 03:23.000
Can we play?!

03:23.000 --> 03:25.000
Sure. What instrument you want to try?

03:25.000 --> 03:28.000
[ Drums playing ] Druuuuums!

03:28.000 --> 03:31.000
Hitting stuff, that is what I am about.

03:31.000 --> 03:33.000
[ Chuckles ] Okay. Let's start with some basics.

03:34.000 --> 03:35.000
This big one down here is the kick.

03:35.000 --> 03:37.000
Hy-aye! [ Boom! ]

03:37.000 --> 03:38.000
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Don't actually kick it.

03:39.000 --> 03:41.000
Just step on that pedal.

03:39.000 --> 03:41.000
[ Drum plays ]

03:41.000 --> 03:42.000
All right, now tap the snare

03:42.000 --> 03:44.000
like you're tapping a pencil.

03:42.000 --> 03:44.000
[ Snare plays ]

03:44.000 --> 03:48.000
Kick, snare. Kick, kick, snare.

03:44.000 --> 03:48.000
[ Drums playing steadily ]

03:49.000 --> 03:51.000
Put your finger here, and with your other hand,

03:51.000 --> 03:53.000
pretend like your fingers are walking on the string.

03:54.000 --> 03:56.000
[ Bass guitar plays ]

03:56.000 --> 03:59.000
There. You're gonna play a power chord.

03:59.000 --> 04:01.000
Heh. You get me.

04:01.000 --> 04:03.000
Now strum!

04:03.000 --> 04:06.000
[ Guitar chord plays ]

04:07.000 --> 04:09.000
Now put your fingers here.

04:09.000 --> 04:10.000
Wh-Whoa.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
[ Rock music playing ]

04:12.000 --> 04:15.000
Together: Whoa!

04:15.000 --> 04:17.000
You're playing a song.

04:17.000 --> 04:20.000
[ Music continues ]

04:21.000 --> 04:22.000
Really? That's it?

04:22.000 --> 04:24.000
Yeah. A song doesn't have to be complicated.

04:24.000 --> 04:27.000
It can be 18 chords or it could be 2.

04:27.000 --> 04:29.000
You guys, all we need is lyrics,

04:29.000 --> 04:31.000
and then we got a hit single for sure!

04:31.000 --> 04:33.000
How do you write lyrics?

04:33.000 --> 04:35.000
Well, you don't need lyrics,

04:35.000 --> 04:36.000
but if there's something you want to express,

04:36.000 --> 04:38.000
whether you totally understand why or not,

04:38.000 --> 04:40.000
it's a way you can keep it from feeling bottled up.

04:40.000 --> 04:42.000
Lyrics are like this thing you want to say,

04:42.000 --> 04:45.000
but maybe you're shy or unsure of yourself.

04:45.000 --> 04:47.000
But by writing those thoughts in a song,

04:47.000 --> 04:48.000
you can be in control.

04:48.000 --> 04:50.000
Yeah, sometimes your song knows how you feel

04:50.000 --> 04:51.000
about something before you do.

04:51.000 --> 04:53.000
[ Badum-tish plays on drums ]

04:53.000 --> 04:54.000
I'm sorry. I thought that was a setup.

04:54.000 --> 04:59.000
Hey! You kids play another note, and I call the cops!

04:59.000 --> 05:00.000
I guess that's it for the day.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.000
[ Lights flick off ]

05:02.000 --> 05:04.000
Oh, hey, we're actually playing a show here on Friday.

05:04.000 --> 05:07.000
If you come up with some lyrics, you could play your song.

05:07.000 --> 05:09.000
That'd be so awesome!

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
Just need some lyrics.

05:11.000 --> 05:18.000
♪♪

05:18.000 --> 05:25.000
♪♪

05:25.000 --> 05:26.000
[ Bird screeches ]

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
Aah!

05:28.000 --> 05:29.000
[ Gasps ]

05:29.000 --> 05:32.000
Oh.

05:33.000 --> 05:36.000
Katie: We could play at that indoor soccer place.

05:36.000 --> 05:37.000
They have shows there sometimes.

05:38.000 --> 05:41.000
Nah. It's a car dealership now.

05:38.000 --> 05:41.000
[ Strumming guitar ]

05:41.000 --> 05:43.000
Oh. We could play that bowling alley.

05:43.000 --> 05:44.000
I've seen shows there.

05:44.000 --> 05:46.000
Nah. It's a diner now.

05:46.000 --> 05:48.000
We could play in the parking lot of that diner.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.000
But then where would we play kickball?

05:50.000 --> 05:51.000
I'm boycotting that diner.

05:52.000 --> 05:54.000
They don't appreciate my views on French fries.

05:54.000 --> 05:57.000
Fries should be bottomless.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.000
Fries  should be bottomless!

05:59.000 --> 06:01.000
Craig: Hey, guys!

06:01.000 --> 06:03.000
[ Panting ] We got some big news.

06:03.000 --> 06:06.000
Yeah. Check out my pants!

06:06.000 --> 06:09.000
I chopped 'em so I got that breezy-leg look

06:06.000 --> 06:09.000
like you guys got.

06:09.000 --> 06:11.000
Also, David, I thought about what you said

06:12.000 --> 06:13.000
about expressing your feelings

06:13.000 --> 06:15.000
and getting it out there and how you can feel better,

06:15.000 --> 06:17.000
and I wrote lyrics for a song.

06:17.000 --> 06:20.000
I put them on this temporary tattoo that I won at a fair.

06:20.000 --> 06:22.000
It's a basketball bunny.

06:22.000 --> 06:23.000
We all want to hear your lyrics,

06:23.000 --> 06:25.000
but it looks like we won't be able

06:25.000 --> 06:26.000
to play music here anymore.

06:26.000 --> 06:27.000
What? Why?

06:27.000 --> 06:30.000
Emma: 'Cause our neighbor's a "not-funster."

06:30.000 --> 06:32.000
He keeps complaining about the noise!

06:32.000 --> 06:33.000
Shh!

06:33.000 --> 06:35.000
We're not even that loud. [ Cymbal plays quietly ]

06:35.000 --> 06:36.000
Shhhh!

06:36.000 --> 06:38.000
[ Whispering ] Also, someone ate Michelle's peanut butter,

06:38.000 --> 06:40.000
and she is not happy.

06:40.000 --> 06:43.000
She's not mad, because it's everybody's,

06:43.000 --> 06:44.000
but, you know...

06:44.000 --> 06:46.000
But -- But what about the show?!

06:46.000 --> 06:48.000
I feel dis-empower-chorded.

06:48.000 --> 06:50.000
Ugh. It's a real bummer.

06:50.000 --> 06:53.000
This garage has been a sanctuary

06:53.000 --> 06:56.000
for the local music scene and our bikes.

06:56.000 --> 06:58.000
I don't know where else we could play last minute like this.

06:59.000 --> 07:01.000
We'd need an isolated spot where we could play

07:01.000 --> 07:04.000
and not bother "Old Man Grumpty Dumpty."

07:04.000 --> 07:07.000
Yeah, I kind of need a hard surface to put my drums on.

07:07.000 --> 07:09.000
With a roof to protect our instruments from the elements

07:09.000 --> 07:11.000
and a big opening so people can see you.

07:11.000 --> 07:14.000
Yeah, we basically need a garage.

07:14.000 --> 07:17.000
Is there a garage in the creek?

07:17.000 --> 07:20.000
JP: No, but there's a rock with a buncha wizards under it.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.000
I think I know a place.

07:22.000 --> 07:23.000
Together: Whoa!

07:23.000 --> 07:26.000
Holy French fries, Bad Moves!

07:26.000 --> 07:27.000
This is so great!

07:27.000 --> 07:29.000
I have way more room for my drums

07:29.000 --> 07:30.000
and room to jump around

07:30.000 --> 07:33.000
and more room to do this!

07:30.000 --> 07:33.000
[ Warble ]

07:33.000 --> 07:36.000
Doesn't seem like this old boy's too moldy, either.

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
Craig, this place is awesome!

07:38.000 --> 07:39.000
What?

07:39.000 --> 07:40.000
I think it could really work!

07:40.000 --> 07:45.000
Yeah! I figured it would fit your specifications!

07:45.000 --> 07:46.000
What?

07:46.000 --> 07:47.000
This is super cool,

07:47.000 --> 07:50.000
but how are we gonna power our instruments?

07:50.000 --> 07:51.000
I'll take care of you guys!

07:51.000 --> 07:56.000
[ Upbeat rock music playing ]

07:56.000 --> 08:04.000
♪♪

08:04.000 --> 08:08.000
♪ I was backed against the traps of my teenage plan ♪

08:09.000 --> 08:12.000
♪ I was stumblin' over gaps, feeling beat up again ♪

08:12.000 --> 08:16.000
♪ I was staring down the corpse of a lifelong dream ♪

08:16.000 --> 08:20.000
♪ I was willing it to get back on its feet again ♪

08:20.000 --> 08:23.000
♪ I was walkin' through my life and feeling sick, that's when ♪

08:23.000 --> 08:27.000
♪ I would find myself repeating my old stories to friends ♪

08:27.000 --> 08:30.000
♪ Always strugglin' for a notion that resembled a hope ♪

08:31.000 --> 08:32.000
♪ I was standing on the verge ♪

08:32.000 --> 08:34.000
♪ Of something good, I don't know ♪

08:32.000 --> 08:34.000
[ Electricity crackles ]

08:35.000 --> 08:39.000
♪ On the verge of something, oh, oh, oh-oh, oh ♪

08:39.000 --> 08:42.000
You know, you guys can go down without me.

08:42.000 --> 08:44.000
Don't let me hold you back

08:44.000 --> 08:46.000
if you want to, like, go down and -- I don't know.

08:46.000 --> 08:49.000
Hey, don't sweat it, Craig. We're loyal.

08:49.000 --> 08:53.000
Besides, look at those chumps, all clumped together,

08:53.000 --> 08:57.000
having a great time, sharing youthful joy.

08:58.000 --> 09:00.000
Who wants that?

09:00.000 --> 09:02.000
♪ Oh, oh, oh-oh, oh ♪

09:02.000 --> 09:06.000
♪ Oh, oh-oh, ohhh ♪

09:06.000 --> 09:08.000
[ Cheers and applause ]

09:08.000 --> 09:10.000
Thanks! And thanks for coming to the show.

09:10.000 --> 09:12.000
I want to remind everyone that we've got some free zines

09:12.000 --> 09:15.000
and merch for sale on that...log back there.

09:15.000 --> 09:17.000
It's really cool to see everyone here

09:17.000 --> 09:19.000
supporting the woodland scene, and we couldn't have done it

09:19.000 --> 09:23.000
without the help of those kids way over there!

09:23.000 --> 09:26.000
Hey, Craig, why don't you come down and play your song!

09:26.000 --> 09:27.000
[ Cheers and applause ]

09:27.000 --> 09:29.000
We don't have to go down there, Craig.

09:29.000 --> 09:31.000
Yeah, man. I mean, we can stay here

09:31.000 --> 09:33.000
in the bird-free zone.

09:33.000 --> 09:34.000
[ Bird screeches ]

09:34.000 --> 09:36.000
Aw, no!

09:36.000 --> 09:46.000
♪♪

09:46.000 --> 09:48.000
[ Guitar plays ]

09:48.000 --> 09:49.000
Um, hi.

09:50.000 --> 09:51.000
W-We are the, uh...

09:51.000 --> 09:53.000
The Cut-Offs!

09:53.000 --> 09:55.000
And The Quantum Axes!

09:55.000 --> 09:57.000
1, 2, 3, 4!

09:57.000 --> 10:00.000
♪ I'm brave, but I'm scared of you ♪

10:00.000 --> 10:05.000
♪ I saw what I thought I knew ♪

10:05.000 --> 10:07.000
♪ You're so much bigger ♪

10:09.000 --> 10:10.000
♪ I'm brave ♪

10:10.000 --> 10:11.000
♪ I'm brave, I'm brave ♪

10:11.000 --> 10:12.000
♪ But I'm scared of you ♪

10:12.000 --> 10:14.000
♪ I saw ♪ -♪ I saw ♪

10:14.000 --> 10:16.000
Wow! They've really improved since two days ago.

10:16.000 --> 10:19.000
Yes! Craig: ♪ So much bigger ♪

10:20.000 --> 10:23.000
Together: ♪ Don't look at me baaaad ♪

10:23.000 --> 10:26.000
♪ Don't look at me baaaad ♪

10:26.000 --> 10:29.000
♪ Don't look at me bad, bad, bad, bad, bad ♪

10:29.000 --> 10:31.000
♪ Don't look at me, bird ♪

10:31.000 --> 10:32.000
[ Gasps ]

10:32.000 --> 10:34.000
Craig, keep going!

10:34.000 --> 10:35.000
You can do this.

10:35.000 --> 10:38.000
[ Music continues ]

10:38.000 --> 10:41.000
♪ Don't look at me bad, bad, bad, bad, bad ♪

10:41.000 --> 10:44.000
♪ Don't look at me, bird ♪

10:44.000 --> 10:48.000
[ Cheers and applause ]

10:50.000 --> 10:52.000
Hey, Craig. What are we gonna call this new place?

10:52.000 --> 10:56.000
Pizza Crust Collective 2? The Silent Barn?

10:56.000 --> 10:58.000
The Not-So-Silent Barn?

10:58.000 --> 11:01.000
Craig: The Vulture's Nest.

11:01.000 --> 11:04.000
♪ When it's time to go to bed ♪

11:04.000 --> 11:09.000
♪ I know I don't have to feel alone ♪

11:09.000 --> 11:12.000
♪ 'Cause I'll see you tomorrow ♪

11:12.000 --> 11:13.000
♪ At the creek ♪

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
Just like I drew it.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
♪♪
